news.title: Signature Global to invest Rs 310 crore on affordable housing project in Gurugram
news.para: The company announced the launch of its new project-Signature Global Imperial spread over 8 acres of land parcel. It is self-funded by the company and is expected to be complete in the next four years.

news.title: Kaisa Group says earnings results delayed due to lockdown, shares slide
news.para: Kaisa late on Tuesday said a virus lockdown in Shenzhen left audit work incomplete so it cannot publish financial results on time. In a filing, it said trading of its shares in Hong Kong will therefore be suspended from April 1 as per bourse rules.

news.title: China Evergrande sets end-July target for restructuring proposal after delaying results
news.para: Evergrande, whose $22.7 billion worth of offshore debt is deemed to be in default, is seeking to "further enhance communications" with creditors to reach the end-July target, its executive director Siu Shawn told investors on a call.

news.title: Maharashtra: Rush before fiscal-end slows down property registrations
news.para: Officials attributed the rush to the property buyers’ intention to get the registration process done before the implementation of 1% metro cess from April 1 and announcement of the new Ready Reckoner rates the same day.

news.title: HDFC Mutual Fund's CIO buys luxury apartment in Mumbai for Rs 19.36 crore
news.para: The apartment spread over a carpet area of 3,692 sq ft is on the 30th floor of the super-premium under construction tower Marina Bay Worli Sea Face.

news.title: PE firms to raise Rs 20,000 crore for affordable, mid-segment residential projects
news.para: The smart recovery in the residential segment has led to the growth of investments. Half a dozen private equity firms focussed on the residential segment are on the road to raise a cumulative Rs 20,000 crore to deploy in the country’s affordable to mid residential segment.

news.title: Housing loan disbursals up by 65% in Gujarat in a year: SLBC
news.para: ​According to the latest report of the State Level Bankers’ Committee (SLBC), the disbursals of fresh loans stood at Rs 11,378 crore in the quarter that ended on December 31, 2021, as compared to Rs 6,907 crore in the corresponding quarter of 2020.

news.title: Cement industry to record 18-20% volume growth in FY22: Report
news.para: However, high input costs on account of inflationary pressure are resulting in a decline in operating margins by 440-480 basis points to around 19.8-20.2 per cent in FY2022, ICRA said.

news.title: HDFC witnesses highest ever loan approval; crosses Rs 2 lakh crore in FY22
news.para: HDFC managing director Renu Sud Karnad said, "In over four and half decades, I have not seen a better time for the housing sector than now due to lower interest rates, stable property prices, government's thrust on affordable housing, improved affordability, favourable demographics, increasing urbanisation and rising aspirations".

news.title: Maharashtra announces stay on NA tax notices to housing societies in Mumbai, Pune
news.para: MLAs cutting across party lines during a calling attention motion moved by BJP legislator Ashish Shelar demanded that the notices be withdrawn and the tax scrapped permanently.

news.title: To avoid razing 735 buildings, part of Metro Line 5 in Bhiwandi to be underground
news.para: The project is currently estimated at Rs 8,417 crore. The issue was raised by Bhiwandi Samajwadi Party MLA Rais Shaikh on Tuesday. He demanded adequate compensation for commercial shops.

news.title: Haryana: Town planner deputed for illegal colony survey sent back
news.para: Before his temporary deputation to the urban local bodies department in Chandigarh, the official, RS Batth, as DTP (enforcement), was overseeing issues related to Chintels Paradiso and NBCC Green View apartments, apart from doing the coordination for the proposed structural audit of five highrises in Gurgaon.

news.title: IndiQube leases one lakh sq ft in Coimbatore
news.para: The company plans to venture into 15 tier II cities in the coming two years for its next phase of growth.

news.title: Property prices to rise by Rs 400-500 per sq ft in Gujarat
news.para: The decision was taken during the board meeting of Credai Gujarat held in Palanpur on Tuesday. Raw material prices have been the bane of real estate developers for a while now.

news.title: New Noida to be developed in four phases
news.para: A draft of the proposed project, which is set to be developed in four phases, is set to be tabled before the Noida Authority in its next board meet, slated to be held later this month or early April. Once cleared, it will be forwarded to the state government for its approval.
